Nobel Prize Winner Steinman Died Friday, Rockefeller Says

-- B y   P h i l   S e r a f i n o
-- 
2011-10-03T13:00:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/nobel-prize-winner-steinman-died-friday-rockefeller-says.html
Ralph M. Steinman, honored today with
a  Nobel Prize  for medicine, died Sept. 30 at the age of 68,
according to Rockefeller University, where he worked.  Steinman was diagnosed with pancreatic cancer four years
ago, and his life was extended using an immunotherapy of his own
design, the New York-based university said in a statement on its
website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Phil Serafino in Paris at 
